Class SemAn.Logger

java.lang.Object
compiler.phase.seman.SemAn.Logger
All Implemented Interfaces:
AST.NullVisitor<Object,Object>, AST.Visitor<Object,Object>, TYP.Visitor<Object,Boolean>
Enclosing class:
SemAn
public static class SemAn.Logger extends Object implements AST.NullVisitor<Object,Object>, TYP.Visitor<Object,Boolean>
Semantic analysis logger. This logger prints out the XML description of semantic attributes that are attached to the abstract syntax tree. It does not traverse the entire abstract syntax tree. Instead, it is used as a Abstr.Logger plug-in.

    • safeAccept

      private void safeAccept(TYP.Type type, Boolean full)
      A wrapper for accepting this visitor. Makes the given type accept this visitor. Unless in development mode where the missing type is replaced by a placeholder, the internal error is thrown if the type is missing, i.e., when null pointer is given instead of an object.
      Parameters:
      type - The type that should accept this visitor.
      full - true if the type should be printed out in-depth or false if the type should be printed with the top-most node only (applicable only for TYP.NameType).
